commit_list.message:
Tests, refactoring, instrumentation + misc improvements (#21)

* Simplify and improve docker/build setup
* Added jitter to command and commit retry delays to reduce load
* Experimental upcasting and lazy transformation support Fixes #23 
* Made the dynamodb table schema slightly more clever (hopefully), allowing for efficient aggregateType + partial aggregateKey queries.
* Only one class: Aggregate (keyless aggregates now have implicit singleton key '@')
* Remove validations - added complexity without providing value
* Efficient Aggregate.eachInstance()
* Helper for clearing snapshots Fixes #14 
* dynamodb.queryCommits() Fixes #15 
* Aggregate#writeSnapshots() Fixes #16 
* Remove BatchWriter Fixes #18 
* Automatically run *.test.js as unit tests and *.test.integration.js as integration tests requiring dynamodb and s3 setup/teardown. Added some test utils to make it easier to deal with commits. Fixes #19 
* Added some tests of core stuff. Still some useful tests missing.
* Removed existing aggregate logging. Added logging and simple instrumentation for commit(), hydrate() and commands. Fixes #20 
* Built code available in dist/ for easier npm publishing
* Updated README

commit_list.message:
Prepare for initial release (#25)

* Improve how executeWorkflow awaits the results - Fixes #20
* Use the same integration tests for both backends - Fixes #21
* Harmonized local/swf backend interfaces (have local backend emulate swf behavior to extent feasable) - Fixes #18
* Improve signal support (incoming and outgoing) - Fixes #22
* Improve configuration interface
* Improved README
* Faster and more dependable integration test setup (each test runs in isolation)
* NPM package should support relevant node versions - fixes #19 
* Support using untranspiled code for node >=9
* Improved workers with concurrency support
* All API functions now prefixes workflowID etc, by default
* Soflow now handles including its own files in lambda packages, allowing developer to specify only app-related files in setup()
* Make setup/teardown faster and more dependable
* SWF activityTask types and workflow types are no longer prefixed by default. Also no more defaults, since they are reused.
* tmux dev session script
commit_list.repo_description: Easily run distributed workflows with AWS Simple Workflow Service and Lambda

commit_list.message:
Improve integration test reliability (#15)

A stab at improving the reliability of the integration tests, as well as some other improvements;

Deciders are now killed upon test completion
Any running workflows are terminated upon test completion
Fix event rule permission bug, decider should now run successfully.
If you use --no-teardown you can now run integration tests back to back and consistently get good results.

After some experimentation, I found that we need to wait for 60 seconds after teardown, for AWS to be ready for a new deploy. This wait can be skipped with --skip-teardown-wait.

commit_list.message:
Allow specifying custom env vars for lambda decider function (#32)

Although there should be no waiting IO activity in deciders like making network
requests, there are still some situations where some logic in the workflows is
dependant on the environment they are running in. As soflow takes responsibility
for deploying the decider lambda, when used in this way it would be convenient
to specify any environment variables that decider should have.

When running you own activity workers this is not an issue since the deployment
is not managed by soflow.
